-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, Oil Refiner Mol Move in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-07-03T15:23:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-oil-refiner-mol-move-in-budapest.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index rose 1.1
percent to 17,461.35 by the close in Budapest.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, advanced
2.1 percent to 3,575 forint. Emerging-market stocks rose on
expectations that central banks from Europe to China will ease
monetary policy to spur growth.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL)  , Hungary’s largest refiner rose 1.6
percent to 16,695 forint. Oil rebounded on speculation sanctions
against Iran will curb supply and that governments will offer
stimulus to boost their economies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  